annotationA: Importin subunit alpha; Protein transmembrane transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein import into nucleus; proteasome assembly; Belongs to the importin alpha family
annotationB: Importin subunit beta; Required for nuclear protein import and mediates docking of import substrate to distinct nucleoporins. In Drosophila, may not function as a snRNP import receptor as it does not interact with components of the snRNP complex such as snRNP U1, U2, U4/U6 and Snup
